It’s been a dream of mine to create in different capacities and share talent in ethereal and tangible objects with my side project, @aokidesigns . Grateful to work with two amazingly talented artists, Carrie @lifearomatherapy who blends natural oils and fragrances into a transforming perfume, and @festino who created a watercolor painting into a gorgeous label with his keen eye for typography and design. I’m happy to share a slice of heaven with primary scent notes of neroli, copal, and amber. Uplifting any mood, encouraging relaxation, grounding, protective and healing, I’d love to introduce “Radiant Being” Eau De Parfum.  I have limited samples to send out as a gift, however I’d be happy to share with those who would like to try.  The first 10 who follow @aokidesigns and DM their name and address, I will send out a small sample. This fragrance is genderless and unisex in nature and will smell different on everyone. A great stocking stuffer for you or a Radiant Being 💫 that you know. ✨❤️🥰
A special thanks to @communionbyjoy who introduced me to Carrie and encourages me on my path. 😘
#radiantbeingperfume #stockingstuffers #naturalfragrance #aokidesigns #smallbusiness #ilovemyjob #giftingseason

Life is pretty good. The twists and turns, introspection, and expectations.  Adapting to a new environment, perhaps it was home 30 years ago?! There are quite a few things I’ve realized about myself. There is also a lot that remains constant. I look back and reflect on my choices.  What led me to move to Seattle, LA, and then NY?  I really had no plan.  I did know I’m curious and perhaps I’m carrying on my fathers spirit of adventure.  I really think DNA has something to do with it.  I’m thirsty for everything, and at the same time, content. Precious moments enjoying nature is one of my most favorite things to do, and I’m so happy I can convince my Mother to go with me.  She’s amazing in so many ways and truly lucky to have her in my life.

There are a few things I’ve been patiently awaiting to acquire, and although a luxury, art is a necessity.  My favorite artist @darrenwaterstonart whom I’ve been following since I lived in Seattle about 20 plus years ago. Starting out eating top ramen for months  and carrying around postcards of art exhibits from Darren in my bag, on my vision board, and as a continued source of inspiration in color and minute detail. Attending openings and meeting once at a San Francisco lecture at the De Young museum. Lark Study in watercolor will finally find a home next month, I’m beyond thrilled!

Feeling lucky to experience a visit to Japan during Sakura season, there’s nothing like the excitement everyone shares 🌸
 #japan #sakuraseason

It took a bit of effort to plan such an epic trip, and was rewarded with beauty difficult to capture. Every sense awakened with the magic of remote rice patty terraces and a waterfall gorge. Thanks to Richard from @yasukoazumajewelry for helping me to figure out some logistics early on in my planning. 🛶

I decided this year to celebrate my birthday by embracing my heritage. 🇯🇵I consider myself now 💯 Japanese.
The kindness of strangers and attention to detail is mind boggling. I am so grateful for every moment. 🙏🏻✨😊
Made all the more special with my Nagoya family @artisan.official @hirokitz @yukistyle22 seeing their beautiful store and celebrating with the finest sushi. How wonderful to meet up with friends to share some amazing moments. Thank you to everyone who made this trip so special ❤️, especially the kindness of strangers.
It’s almost a blur but I’ve decided to write about it

Happy Fathers Day to all the rad dads out there!  And for the brave mothers who married these adventurous spirits!  Sometimes I didn’t appreciate the experience completely when I was up tarring rooftops in Alaska or working in the garden doing some manual labor, but Now I do!  I learned the importance of hard work  and the enjoyment in creating a vision. I always had a carpenter tool belt working along side my Father as a little girl. My Dad was an absolute dreamer which I completely relate to and whenever I find myself feeling adventurous I know I’m channeling his spirit and that I’m on the right path. It wasn’t always easy growing up Asian American in Utah, going to war and being an underdog.  Nothing really stopped the ideas flowing, and caring what other people think, another quality I seemed to inherit. He loved nature like no other, had the warmest heart, was nicknamed “Sumo” and had a laugh that was contagious.  All I can say is each year I am so thankful to have some dna and memories of him that seem to live on wirhin me. ✨🥰❤️
